Psychology of trumpeting: Why waste more money?
In auctions, customers are willing to spend more money, value goods.
The neurological and economic foundations of this well-known - and apparently irrational - behavior have been able to reveal to researchers in the field of neurology and the economy of New York University.
According to their study, published in Science magazine, people do not want to stay in the eBay auction competition, so they'd rather pay too high a price.
Research using experimental auction tried to map the scheme of this "game" in the nervous system.
One group of volunteers sat, the other group participated in playful auctions, using a method of functional magnetic resonance (fMRI) examined the active area of the brain of subjects.
In both games, participants were able to win money, but in the auction game, which is an important element to break down the other side, they began to work intensively when losing a whole that is under the brain core, called striatum.
This brain area plays in addition to many other functions in the "self-rewarding" mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to researchers, it is possible to explain how to avoid direct street reactions.
To support their theory, members of the research team from a number of economics carried out financial cross-border research.
Under different conditions, he was tried against one partner by three groups.
The control group was simply informed of the actual value of the product concerned and they made the bets.
In addition, members of the other group were promised that if they quit the winning game, they would get another $15.
On the other hand, the third group received 15 dollars before the auction, but in the event of a loss, its members also lost this money.
So the difference between the two groups was all about winning and losing.
However, members of the group playing "against the loss" were willing to go higher than it was in the control and "victory" group, which confirms the hypothesis of neurologists.
"These results cannot be derived from any previously existing economic theory.
For so far, they have explained the phenomena that can be seen in the auctioning joys of winning and avoiding risk.
When neurological imaging methods helped us to resolve the difference between these two theories, we now have a third explanation," observed Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics of New York University.
Hepatitis: When to find a doctor?
About half a billion people worldwide suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C infection, then in Hungary this chronic liver disease is listed among the major causes of death.
The number of home cases of hepatitis is estimated to be hundreds of thousands, but only seven thousand of them are treated, which is why the patient often does not know they are infected.
The name of hepatitis is the summary name of the infection caused by various viruses.
In their symptoms there are many similarities, there are signs of inflammation of the liver and the liver, but the origins of the disease and their underlying disease differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses are spread in two main ways: hepatitis type A and E with lawnmowers (e.g. food, water infected), hepatitis type B, C, D and other blood and fluid viruses (sperms, secretion, spleen).
Travellers should in any case be protected by vaccination against A and B virus, and no vaccine C virus exists.
Hepatitis A symptoms occur two to three weeks after eating the infected food, usually caused by nausea, weakness, abdominal problems, vomiting.
Then, on the skin and eye whites, a yellowish, bright stools and cloudy urine are formed. The treatment can last for two to three weeks.
Every year millions of people worldwide die from the most serious type of this disease, from liver cancer and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B.
The main reason for this is that according to estimates, only every tenth infected drug is treated.
Hepatitis C may also have very serious consequences: if it is not treated, it may lead to liver cirrhosis or cancer of the liver.
Most people who are infected with their disease don't even know, the origin of the disease destroys the liver cells eventually, so the first symptoms are delivered in many cases up to 20-30 years.
This is why timely prevention, regular testing is very important.
In three groups, this disease occurs more frequently than on average: between people who had undergone blood transfusions before 1991, between drug users and people with tattoos.
At present, the estimated global number of individuals infected with chronic hepatitis C 200 million is estimated.
Since disease can prove an already routine laboratory test, a person should, in case of any sign of unknown origin, refer to his or her doctor.
In early detection, the disease is therapeutic, the virus can be removed from the body, thus preventing infection and preventing cancer.
September 30 is the World Day of Hepatitis, which was organized by the organizations representing the disease for the first time worldwide in 2004.
Its aim is to highlight the chronic inflammation of the liver caused by these viruses, the causes of its emergence and the importance of early detection of the disease.
